<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Rampage</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
by Bombudil<br>
<br>
Higher level mobs have something called rampage lists. A rampage list is like a second hate/aggro list, but it works in weird ways:<br>
<br>
Rampage is an extra round of attacks a mob can make. It will not rampage each battle-round, but every so often the mob is going to smack the person on the top of Rampage around.<br>
<br>
Once you are on the Rampage list, you cannot get off. Even if you die and get rezzed back you are still on the list.<br>
<br>
Even stranger: Once you are in position X on a rampage list, you stay there. <br>
<br>
Rampage lists are not dynamic like hate/aggro, they are permanent.<br>
<br>
On to the point:<br>
<br>
Before a battle, a chanter will often memblur a mob. Memblur deletes hate/aggro lists as well as Rampage lists.<br>
<br>
If our friend the ranger fires a shot at this mob now, (s)he will enter the Rampage list at the top (and stay there for eternity, or until mob is dead, or chanter has to memblur again).<br>
<br>
Raids will have designated Rampage tanks (and rampage healers - druids, this is something which will be your job) If you are not the designated rampage tank, and get on the rampage list, you have just screwed everyone else over.<br>
<br>
An extreme example is the Arch Lich of the Temple of Ssraezcha. This pleasant fellow (a snake actually, or a Shissar to be exact) does so much Rampage that a second CH rotation is needed just to keep the Rampage tank alive. 2 CH rotations running in parallell!<br>
<br>
That's it from Advanced Raiding 101 for today <!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--> <p><center>
